  "texts": [
    "IntroductionThe rapid advancement of artificial intelligence has brought forth a new era of large language models (LLMs), which have demonstrated remarkable capabilities in natural language understanding and generation.",
    "However, despite their impressive performance, LLMs often suffer from issues related to factual inaccuracy.",
    "The propensity of LLMs to generate incorrect or misleading information poses significant challenges, particularly when these models are employed in applications where accuracy and reliability are paramount.",
    "This problem is exacerbated by the fact that LLMs rely heavily on the vast amounts of data they are trained on, which may contain inaccuracies, outdated information, or biases.",
    "Consequently, addressing the issue of factual inaccuracy in LLMs has become a critical area of research."
  ],
